On Sat, 19 Jun 1999, Richard Gooch wrote:
> Actually, devfs makes it better. Devfs allows you to have a shared
> NFS read-only root and still have a mutable /dev. And you can have
> persistence too!
Or you can have a root NTFS and still have a workable /dev even though
NTFS doesnt support device files. Admittedly a strange case but devfs
handles it elegantly
